 Dhaka, Feb 8 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh lost the three-match ODI series against New Zealand after suffering a five-wicket defeat in the second game at University Oval in Dunedin on Monday. Chasing 184 for victory, the Black Caps reached their target (185-5) in 27.3 overs. Ross Taylor led the charge with a 52-ball 78 that contained six fours and five sixes. He was later named man of the match. Besides, Martin Guptill scored 32, Peter Ingram made 28 and James Franklin remained 20 not out. Shafiul Islam and Rubel Hossain shared five wickets. Earlier, Mushfiqur Rahim's fighting half-century pulled the Tigers out of a precarious 46-6 to a respectable 183-8 in 50 overs. Mushfiq slammed 86 off 107 deliveries with eight fours and three sixes and featured in a 101-run seventh stand with Naeem Islam, who made 43. Put into bat, the top-order was torn to shreds inside the first 25 overs. Tail-ender Shahadat Hossain added 16 runs off seven balls while Aftab Ahmed, who made a painstaking 27-ball 10, were the only other two batsmen able to get into double figures. Ian Butler and Andy McKay shared five wickets. Daryl Tuffey was the other Kiwi wicket-taker. Bangladesh will be looking now to salvage some pride in the third match in Christchurch on Feb 11. The tourists lost the first ODI by 146 runs at McLean Park in Napier on Fr
